name: MTLLibraryError
desc: Errors returned by Metal for library errors.

items.name: var errorCode: Int
items.desc: The error code that can result from the creation of Metal library or Metal function object.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A string containing the localized description of the error.

items.name: static var unsupported: MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: Metal couldn’t support the requested action.

items.name: static var `internal`: MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: The action caused an internal error.

items.name: static var compileFailure: MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: The library or function failed to compile.

items.name: static var compileWarning: MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: The library or function compiled successfully but generated warnings.

items.name: static var fileNotFound: MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: Metal couldn’t find the Metal source file.

items.name: static var functionNotFound: MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: Metal couldn’t find the specified Metal function.

items.name: static var errorDomain: String
items.desc: The error domain used by Metal when returning library or function creation errors.

items.name: static func != (MTLLibraryError, MTLLibraryError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two library errors aren’t equal.

items.name: enum MTLLibraryError.Code
items.desc: Error codes returned by Metal for library errors.
